cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the performance issues in Wi-Fi networks and proposes solutions to mitigate collisions, which are related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the MAC protocols used in IEEE 802.11, which are related to information theory and communication systems, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The paper also mentions security issues, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses future trends in MAC protocols, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
